      "id": "tutorial-ssh-keys-01",
      "markerIndex": 0,
      "replayStartSec": 1.626287,
      "replayEndSec": 6.456735,
      "narrationText": "First, generate a new SSH key on your laptop. Ed25519 is secure, small, and well supported. You do this once; the same key works for every server you add. This is plain SSH, independent of any tooling here.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-ssh-keys/tutorial-ssh-keys-01.d9e3eb30.mp3",
      "textHash": "d9e3eb3031398f29505093133a919c00fc82417b87626d1bc574efd86046a593",
      "audioDurationSec": 16.927347,
      "afterAudioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-ssh-keys/tutorial-ssh-keys-01-after.35e2a62c.mp3",
      "afterAudioDurationSec": 3.709388,
      "afterTextHash": "35e2a62c80dce929f07bb86575c2755ab1ca3e4c7fc130ca2418834e171866ee"
    },
    {
      "id": "tutorial-ssh-keys-02",
      "markerIndex": 1,
      "replayStartSec": 6.456735,
      "replayEndSec": 13.33617,
      "narrationText": "Now authorize the key on your first server with ssh-copy-id. It appends your public key to the server's authorized list, so future logins skip the password.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-ssh-keys/tutorial-ssh-keys-02.1290a416.mp3",
      "textHash": "1290a4169f720cf49ab3dbb01ad781337534ebf7be0f1bbf3afc3aa4873ce986",
      "audioDurationSec": 10.762449,
      "afterAudioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-ssh-keys/tutorial-ssh-keys-02-after.7acc6fe5.mp3",
      "afterAudioDurationSec": 3.552653,
      "afterTextHash": "7acc6fe541a4697c14eeb95a1728982645fdc02cb6c5350d285cfdfbbf89cdf3"
    },
    {
      "id": "tutorial-ssh-keys-03",
      "markerIndex": 2,
      "replayStartSec": 13.33617,
      "replayEndSec": 19.159643,
      "narrationText": "Do the same for every other server you manage. Here we authorize the second one. Just repeat ssh-copy-id for each machine.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-ssh-keys/tutorial-ssh-keys-03.31167cec.mp3",
      "textHash": "31167cec061931d5a906821feda37668ab6bdccf63f10e0b9923b326670b8646",
      "audioDurationSec": 8.672653,
      "afterAudioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-ssh-keys/tutorial-ssh-keys-03-after.aab5eaf4.mp3",
      "afterAudioDurationSec": 3.866122,
      "afterTextHash": "aab5eaf4cc5f2ab1c0f01588cf3741c1c7611f7bf1953a3f00f432e0eff0cefa"
    }
  ],
  "narrationAudio": [
    {
      "id": "intro",
      "textHash": "81ac38a9650ac8e79d9c844ba6f5fa737e33c91eaaf57e93d16d3fe7e64b476c",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-ssh-keys/intro.81ac38a9.mp3",
      "narrationText": "Alright! Let's set up SSH keys so you can reach your servers without passwords. This is pure SSH; rdc isn't involved yet.",
      "audioDurationSec": 8.437551
    },
    {
      "id": "three-steps-generate-copy-register",
      "textHash": "a1b96f221c5f062461b2362c843ada618e4d5715b9befcfb2d9f4142c0911699",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-ssh-keys/three-steps-generate-copy-register.a1b96f22.mp3",
      "narrationText": "Two ideas. Generate one key on your laptop, then authorize it on each server with ssh-copy-id. Generate once, copy per server.",
      "audioDurationSec": 10.44898
    },
    {
      "id": "next-tutorial",
      "textHash": "fb33610ec7ff47b1fd6aa3a49928a3154448169026997a85b3271b9f79a68f98",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-ssh-keys/next-tutorial.fb33610e.mp3",
      "narrationText": "Your key is set and your servers trust it. Next up, we add your first server to rdc.",
